  "prompt": "Without any external help, how many pennies can you stack before the tower collapses?",
  "response": "The number of pennies you can stack before the tower collapses depends on several factors such as the surface you are stacking them on, the condition of the pennies, and how carefully you stack them. On a flat, stable surface with careful stacking, you could potentially stack hundreds of pennies before the tower becomes unstable and collapses. However, for most people, a practical limit might be somewhere between 100 and 200 pennies, as the tower becomes more prone to tipping over from slight movements or imperfections as it gets taller.",
